Hi, Diane.

As Diane wrote to Dr. Math
On 09/20/2004 at 21:45:46 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>What number has 642 in the ones period and 739 in the thousands 
>period
>
>[Difficulty]
>don't know what is meant by period
>
>[Thoughts]
>739 (thousands) 642 (ones)
>7006 + 3004 + 9002 = 19,012

A period is a group of three digits. The groups are customarily 
separated by commas (in the U.S.). Thus in your number, 19 is in the 
thousands period and 12 is in the ones period.

No, I didn't learn this term as a student, either.

See this item in the Dr. Math Archives:

  Placement of Commas in Writing Numbers
  http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/view/64292.html

